  "prompt": "Who is the best doctor for cardiology in India?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" doctor can be subjective and depends on specific needs and criteria, such as experience, patient reviews, medical accomplishments, and specialization within cardiology. However, several Indian cardiologists are widely recognized for their expertise and contributions to the field. Notable names include:\n\n1. **Dr. Devi Prasad Shetty** - Founder of Narayana Health, he is highly reputed for his contributions to affordable cardiac care and surgery.\n\n2. **Dr. Naresh Trehan** - A renowned cardiovascular and cardiothoracic surgeon, he is the Chairman and Managing Director of Medanta - The Medicity.\n\n3. **Dr. Ramakanta Panda** - Known for his expertise in beating heart surgery, he is Vice Chairman and Managing Director of the Asian Heart Institute in Mumbai.\n\n4. **Dr. Ashok Seth** - Chairman of Fortis Escorts Heart Institute, New Delhi, he is recognized globally for his work in interventional cardiology.\n\n5. **Dr. Balram Bhargava** - Not only a leading cardiologist but also the former Director General of the Indian Council of Medical Research (ICMR).\n\nWhen choosing a cardiologist, it's essential to consider their specialization relevant to your needs, the hospital's reputation, distance, and cost, as well as recommendations from patients or other healthcare providers.",
